    • Content

      * Model 2b, comply PT
* maximum likelihood estimation of risk attitudes (CRRA utility) under PT (Tversky and Kahneman 1992)
* U(x) = (x^(1-r))/(1-r)
* allows for subjects to make structural error in the comparison of the two EUs
* (Harrison, List, Towe; Econometrica 2007)

clear all
cd "C:\Documents and Settings\Redzo\Desktop\current Research\risk aversion"
capture log close
log using complyPT.log, replace
use risk_aversion9.dta, clear

* (gains and) losses in 'compliance' choices

gen y=21 
* revenue in each period (fixed)- this is the 'Reference point'

* ML program 
program define ML_complyPT
args lnf alpha beta lambda gamma noise

tempvar comply cominsprop comcost comfine y
tempvar prob1 prob2 prob3 prob4 m1 m2 m3 m4 u1 u2 u3 u4 euC euN euDiff tmp

quietly{
* initialize the data
generate int `comply' = $ML_y1
generate double `cominsprop' = $ML_y2
generate double `comcost' = $ML_y3
generate double `comfine' = $ML_y4
generate double `y' = $ML_y5

generate double `tmp' = ((1^`gamma')+((1-1)^`gamma'))^(1/`gamma')
gen double `prob1' = (1^`gamma')/`tmp'
gen double `prob2' = (0^`gamma')/`tmp'

replace `tmp' = (($ML_y2^`gamma')+((1-$ML_y2)^`gamma'))^(1/`gamma')
gen double `prob3' = ($ML_y2^`gamma')/`tmp'
gen double `prob4' = ((1-$ML_y2)^`gamma')/`tmp'

generate double `m1' = `y'-`comcost' 
generate double `m2' = 0
generate double `m3' = `y'-`comfine' 
generate double `m4' = `y'

* utility functions

gen double `u1' = . 
replace `u1' = (`m1'^(1-`alpha'))/(1-`alpha') if `m1'>=21
replace `u1' = -`lambda'*(-`m1'^(1-`beta'))/(1-`beta') if `m1'<21

gen double `u2' = . 
replace `u2' = (`m2'^(1-`alpha'))/(1-`alpha') if `m2'>=21
replace `u2' = -`lambda'*(-`m2'^(1-`beta'))/(1-`beta') if `m2'<21 

gen double `u3' = . 
replace `u3' = (`m3'^(1-`alpha'))/(1-`alpha') if `m3'>=21
replace `u3' = -`lambda'*(-`m3'^(1-`beta'))/(1-`beta') if `m3'<21

gen double `u4' = . 
replace `u4' = (`m4'^(1-`alpha'))/(1-`alpha') if `m4'>=21
replace `u4' = -`lambda'*(-`m4'^(1-`beta'))/(1-`beta') if `m4'<21

gen double `euC' = (`prob1'*`u1') + (`prob2'*`u2')
gen double `euN' = (`prob3'*`u3') + (`prob4'*`u4')

generate double `euDiff' = (`euC'-`euN')/`noise'

* evaluate the likelihood
quietly replace `lnf' = ln(normal(`euDiff')) if `comply'==1
quietly replace `lnf' = ln(1-normal(`euDiff')) if `comply'==0
}
end
ml model lf ML_complyPT (alpha: comply cominsprop comcost comfine y = dem_age dem_econ dem_female dem_stats dem_uniyear) (beta: ) (lambda: ) (gamma: ) (noise:), cluster(expuniqid) technique(nr) 
ml check
ml search
ml maximize, difficult

ml query
ml search /alpha .01 5 /beta .001 5 /lambda .01 5 /gamma .01 5 /noise .01 5
ml query
ml maximize


ml search /alpha .18 2 /beta .45 2 /lambda 1.52 2 /gamma 1.18 2 /noise 1.66 2

 1.660263
*/

ml graph

* test of parameter estimates

test [alpha]_cons = [beta]_cons

test [lambda]_cons = 1

test [gamma]_cons = 1
